					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Eh, I generally only ever used scope to solve name conflict issues that already existed when trying to modify stuff I'd already written. For new code I don't tend to need scope at all, and only occasionally want to use proc, though I make heavy use of local labels (@/:).<br /><br />Like, it's a useful feature when I need it, but I don't go out of my way to put everything in its own scope, etc. If proc isn't really appropriate for the way you use your subroutines, why use it at all for those ones? You're going out of your way to put a simple inside a scope, and then doing more work to take it out of that scope at the end.<br /><br />Hmm, actually I'm wondering, do you know about <a href="http://cc65.github.io/doc/ca65.html#ss6.4" class="postlink">local labels</a>? They're basically the reason I don't really find much need for scope/proc.</div>

