						<div class="postbody">Just found another very bizarre bug: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://github.com/cc65/cc65/issues/235">https://github.com/cc65/cc65/issues/235</a><!-- m --><br /><br />I was using symbols to keep track of what macros were doing, but everything broke when I started using those macros inside scopes... Turns out that expressions don't look for symbols in outer scopes. In this particular case, it seems I can make the symbols global and access them with ::, but that definitely sounds like a bug to me.</div>

