						<div class="postbody">It doesn't know that you aren't going to redefine (and shadow) <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">Symbol</tt> later in the same scope. Perhaps a better rule would be the one fo-fo suggested in a reply: use in a constant expression forbids shadowing of the same variable name later in any enclosing scope.</div>

